HEADWORD: Placental
<hw>Pla*cen"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the placenta; having, or characterized by having, a
placenta; <as>as, a <ex>placental</ex> mammal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
Placentalia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placental</ent>⟦br⟧

